# Copy to .env and fill in. dashboard/.env is gitignored.
#
# For local development against the local Supabase stack (supabase start),
# use the values it prints -- API_URL and PUBLISHABLE_KEY. The local
# publishable key is a well-known, published default (same for every local
# Supabase project everywhere), not a real secret -- it's the SECRET_KEY
# (or legacy SERVICE_ROLE_KEY) that's sensitive and must never go in a
# VITE_-prefixed variable, since Vite inlines those into the public bundle.
#
# For the real cloud project, get these from Supabase dashboard -> Project
# Settings -> API. Supabase's newer key format uses "Publishable key"
# (sb_publishable_...) in place of the older JWT-format "anon key" -- both
# fill the same role (safe to expose in browser code; RLS is what actually
# restricts access) and both work with createClient(). This project uses
# the newer publishable-key naming.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
